The paper deals with localization of a robot in indoor environments using scan matching point clouds captured by a Kinect depth camera. This falls under the domain of robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of motion sensors and data fusion techniques also suggests the involvement of machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the development of Invariant Extended Kalman Filter (IEKF) and Multiplicative Extended Kalman Filter (MEKF) solutions indicates the use of estimation and optimization techniques, which are commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
